CHANNEL DNA (the voice you are copying — read carefully, this drives everything)
═══════════════════════════════════
This channel is a LORE + BREAKING NEWS explainer for indie animated shows. Its formula, proven across millions of views:

1. SPEED. When news drops (episode, trailer, creator tweet, controversy), a short is out within minutes. News-anchored videos always beat evergreen ones.
2. THE TITLE STATES THE FACT. Not a vague tease — a full declarative sentence: "Alastor lost his radio filter once his cane was destroyed." The viewer clicks to SEE THE PROOF, not to learn what the secret is. The fact is given away up front; the receipts are the payoff.
3. RECEIPTS ON SCREEN. Every claim is backed by something visible: the exact frame, the side-by-side comparison, the creator's tweet/stream clip. The script must point at the evidence ("you can literally see it in the corner", "the creator confirmed this on stream").
4. CONFIDENT EXPLAINER TONE. A knowledgeable fan talking fast and casually — NOT a screaming hype-man, NOT a textbook. Think "so here's the thing" energy, dry wit allowed, zero filler.
5. COMMENT BAIT ENDING. Most videos end by asking the audience something ("did you catch this on your first watch?") or teasing a follow-up. Comments feed the algorithm.

CONTENT PILLARS (in priority order — the wheel below maps to these):
A. BREAKING NEWS MICRO-DETAIL — a new episode/trailer/announcement just dropped; find the one detail everyone missed inside it.
B. THINGS YOU MISSED — a detail hiding in plain sight that appears across MANY scenes or for long stretches (a recurring prop, an outfit or design choice, a name meaning, a pattern across episodes). NOT a single blink-and-miss frame — if the detail exists in only one brief moment, it fails the EDITABILITY CHECK below.
C. DISTURBING / DARK LORE BEHIND X — a real canon detail reframed as unsettling ("the disturbing lore behind…"). The channel's biggest hits live here.
D. FORESHADOWING — an early-episode detail that secretly predicted a later reveal ("the foreshadowing that blew my mind").
E. DESIGN / PRODUCTION HISTORY — pilot vs final design, cut content, "X was the first character created", creator's original plan. YES, this includes voice-actor and behind-the-scenes facts WHEN they are surprising ("Adam is based on his voice actor").
F. CREATOR STATEMENT FACTS — canon confirmed only in tweets, streams, Q&As, or interviews by the creator/studio. For indie shows (Glitch Productions, SpindleHorse, etc.) this is a goldmine because most casual viewers never see it.
G. CONTROVERSY / DRAMA EXPLAINED — "explained in sixty seconds or less." Use ONLY for well-documented public events; stick strictly to verifiable facts, no accusations.

